                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/215: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-27T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 27, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>447. Department’s instruction No. 1454 of January 18, 1930. Please inform the
                    Minister that the Department would welcome an expression of his views with
                    regard to the question of extra-settlement roads at Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
